         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>154</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>73</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they have ordered to write accompanied by a stamp ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>149</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>114</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having enterd into the harem</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">as the rising sun in the morning, this glorious being ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">a sandal-coloured monk’s robe ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... up to the region of the highest class of Śuddhāvāsakāyika gods ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>98 and n.4</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">he laughs [and] chats with these (women of the palace) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>403</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>46</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... even a woman makes the wish to be the wife of this one ///</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels">MaitrHami 13, 1-2</note><note type="philcomment">This fragment contains the end of the twelfth and the beginning of the thirteenth act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka. The colophon of act 12 is contained in line a1, act 13 begins in line a2f. An Uy. parallel to the latter is MaitrHami 13, 1a5-2a11. See also <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1999"/><citedRange>200-201</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">Fragment of a manuscript which includes <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a251"/> - <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a294"/> (cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:gengetal2004a"/><citedRange>64-65</citedRange></bibl>).</note></p>
         </div>
